Questions that arise after the accident: Are stewards in the bus illegal?
The law ignores them; walking in a long distance car is forbidden
In the context of the tragic crash of the Student Agency bus near Padua, Italy, the question arises whether stewards and passengers can move inside the bus during the journey.
"If we wanted to strictly and formally comply with the law, the activity of a steward is contrary to the law on road traffic," said transport ministry spokesman Karel Hanzelka.
The accident in question, during which a 22-year-old stewardess died, was apparently caused by the driver of a truck that crossed the path of the coach.
The girl was sadly sitting next to the driver, in the most dangerous seat in the vehicle, although she had two more seats at her disposal.
However, the coach can have an accident, or even brake abruptly, also at the time when the steward serves coffee or distributes newspapers.
What matters is whether the coach is under its data sheet equipped with standing seats or not.
If this standing seating equipment is not approved, passengers must remain seated.
Student Agency long-distance coaches do not have standing seats; this was confirmed at Aktuáln<0xC4><0x9B>.cz by the company director Radim Jan<0xC4><0x8D>ura.
"This is an issue that we have dealt with the ministry and, at first, it prohibits any movement of passengers.
Then they canceled it and we got passengers to go to the toilet during the journey as long as they had their own seat,” he said.
The law ignores the steward
“There is no unequivocal legal interpretation of the role of steward – no legal prescription deals with this role.
On the other hand, no legal requirement prohibits the carrier from offering services.
The road transport law knows only the term "vehicle receiver"; it does not define his rights and duties," Hanzelka adds more ambiguously.
Josef Pokorn<0xC3><0xBD>, the director of the road traffic department, believes, on the contrary, that the law sufficiently addresses the problem.
"It all depends on whether the bus has permission to offer standing seats in its approval.
It's all in there," he said.
The coaches are divided into urban, where there are standing seats and a limited maximum speed, intercity with standing seats and a higher allowed speed and in long distance coaches without standing seat with the highest allowed maximum speed and seats equipped with seat belts.
Like on the plane, says an expert
Jaroslav Ho<0xC5><0x99>ín, an expert at BESIP (road traffic safety) in transport safety, does not see the movement of stewards on board as a major problem.
"In regular traffic, there is no danger. The situation can be compared to that of service in aircraft.
Neither is it certain when turbulence will occur and the air hostess may hit her head."
“In the event that the bus braked abruptly, the laws of physics would obviously be valid.
In the same way as in an urban bus or in a tram.
The carrier must manage the safety of the stewards by internal prescriptions," he says and also believes that from the point of view of the law, the problem is not solved.
Jan<0xC4><0x8D>ura is ready to remove these services
Student Agency is the only coach carrier to offer stewardship services.
He's hiring two hundred.
Even after this accident, the director does not consider their job as a risky job.
"However, as soon as I get the impression that this is a risky trade, I will remove it.
Passengers can receive their coffee and newspaper on boarding.
It would also reduce costs," he said.
The safety concern is the reason for the absence of stewards in his vehicles the director of the Asiana Alexei Litvine, which ensures, in comparison with SA, a very small number of lines.
"We don't have hostesses. We have opposed them from the beginning.
Sooner or later it will end in a fatal accident," he told T<0xC3><0xBD>den.cz a year ago.
A huge tragedy has happened
A young hostess from the Plze<0xC5><0x88> region, who had been working for the company for two years, died in the accident on the Naples line.
A Slovenian truck probably left the emergency stop strip without using a flasher and blocked the way to the bus.
The latter's driver tried to avoid it by means of a sudden maneuver, but he brushed it on his right side.
Jan<0xC4><0x8D>ura refuses that the two seats reserved for the rest of the stewards have been sold.
"In the case of long-distance lines, it is not possible to book these places, they are blocked."
The company intends to file a complaint against the driver of the truck.
For the compensation of the family of the girl, the agency will not wait for the judgment of the court, but as for the financial compensation, it also counts on the culprit.
An amendment to the law?
Not in sight
An amendment to the law, which has been being drafted for more than a year by a group of 30 experts from the Ministry of Transport, could provide clarification on the movements of the stewards on board the bus.
"But it has not come to any conclusion on this point.
In fact, she is not interested in buses, but rather in the points system, maximum speed on the highway and the use of the mobile phone at the wheel," says Ho<0xC5><0x99>ín.
"The Ministry of Transport does not see the activity of the stewards as something that would fundamentally jeopardize the safety of passengers," concludes spokesman Hanzelka, noting that the control of the safety of the buses is under the power of the police and the office for occupational safety.
