It is not dance or singing in itself, but the personality and character of the artist who captivates the audience with his art.
The search for the essential and the magic has been the constant of this work that we present these days at the El Fotómata gallery.
Flamenco stars such as Diego El Cigala, Chano Lobato, Cristina Hoyos, Enrique Morente, El Lebrijano, Antonio Canales, Vicente Amigo, among others, are part of the selection made from about seventy photographed artists.
The project has evolved into an anthology of flamenco, which will soon be published in a book collection of portraits exhibited at the gallery.
Bauer's passion for portraiture led him to repeat the idea two years ago with the "Portraits of old athletes" ("SportARTproject").
Although the concepts are different in "Flamenco - people", the photographer admits that he loves to photograph people's portraits, get to know them and be able to enter their lives for a longer or shorter time.
I think that in photography the portrait is the most difficult genre.
You find yourself in front of people, characters that sometimes you do not know or that leave you only a few minutes to be able to take a picture of them.
Despite these circumstances, as a photographer, I’m still trying to make my ideas come true.”
This collection of portraits of the current flamenco that is entitled "Flamenco - people", is exhibited at the El Fotómata Gallery, located at number 20 of rue de la Mata (street parallel to the People's Square of Hercules) which will be open until October 16.
