Open Office, this is the third edition of the "anti-Microsoft" package
This is the release day of OpenOffice.org.3.0, the open source suite of personal productivity that aims to reach more and more users, from home to office, from professionals to public administration, offering a free alternative to the most famous Microsoft Office.
After almost a year of work, carried out by volunteer developers, supervised by SUN Microsystem, the new Open Office package is shown to the general public with various novelties: from the welcome screen, and the interface revised and become less austere, to others more important, such as the compatibility born for the operating system Apple Mac OS X, and the support for the new ODF format.
Open Office has paid particular attention to the interaction with the Office 2007 suite, and it is indeed possible to open documents with the new Microsoft extension (.docx, .xlsx, .pptx.)
Also interesting are some functions specific to certain modules, such as the one that allows to reduce the dimensions of PowerPoint presentations, useful for example, to send them by email, or to import PDF files into the graphics module, preserving the original appearance of the page.
Still on this front, it is possible to create "hybrid PDF" documents that join the typical Adobe format graph to the elements of a spreadsheet or a text editor.
The collaboration between several people is an element that has had various improvements within the applications: in the spreadsheet, various users can intervene, avoiding conflicts on the changes, in the development of texts, because each collaborator is assigned a color of comments for better recognition during the review phase.
Some companies are even working to bring certain OpenOffice features to the web (on the cloud), and in the coming weeks, they are expected to release the final result.
The Italian version can be downloaded at http://it.openoffice.org/download/3.0.0/download300.html and is in addition to the English version that was on the mirror since Friday.
In addition to Windows and Mac OS, the suite is as usual also available for the Linux operating system.
On request, the installation CD can be shipped to your home or workplace.
And if the theme of free can be a way to spread it in the homes, it is precisely in the business, that Open Office the suite tries the great challenge, can already count on various projects carried out in the public administration and schools.
Not to mention the realities that offer a training, consulting and assistance service, ideal for small and medium-sized enterprises, which could also open up to business prospects.
Open Office consists of five main modules: Writer, for video writing equivalent of Word; Calc, is the spreadsheet that aims to replace Excel; Impress, for rival PowerPoint presentations; Dbase, such as the famous Access, is the program that allows you to work on databases; finally Drwa is the graphics module.
Objective for 2008, reach 5 million downloads, and considering that today there are almost 3 million and 600 miles, it is likely that with the release of the new version, we can even exceed the expected figure
